.TH CRYPT.SH 1 "27 Feb 2006" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"
        
.SH NAME
crypt.sh, encrypt \- encrypt files received from \fBrdup -c\fR

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B crypt.sh
.IR KEYFILE
[
.IR -d
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcrypt.sh\fR encrypts the data it receives from \fBrdup\fR with the
key contained in \fIKEYFILE\fR.
.PP
For example,
.PP
        rdup -c list ~/Documents | crypt.sh KEY | mirror.sh -c -b /tmp/storage
.PP
Note the \fI-c\fR option for \fBmirror.sh\fR.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d
decrypt the files

.SH SEE ALSO
gzip.sh(1) and mirror.sh(8).
